WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:03.298
The FX original series,
The Americans.

00:03.330 --> 00:05.628
The new season,
Wednesdays at 10:00 on FX.

00:08.370 --> 00:09.803
PREVIOUSLY ON
"THE AMERICANS"...

00:09.840 --> 00:11.637
LISTEN, KIMMY,
THIS WHOLE AGE THING...

00:11.670 --> 00:12.978
WHEN PEOPLE SEE US TOGETHER,
IT'S WEIRD.

00:13.010 --> 00:14.807
LET'S JUST HANG OUT
IN PRIVATE.

00:14.840 --> 00:16.148
Elizabeth: YOU'LL GET IN THERE

00:16.180 --> 00:17.807
AND SEE WHAT
YOU HAVE TO WORK WITH.

00:17.850 --> 00:20.671
WHAT I HAVE TO WORK WITH IS
A HORMONAL 15-YEAR-OLD GIRL.

00:20.720 --> 00:23.188
WHEN YOU WERE ADMITI'ED
TO THE ACADEMY, I WAS PREGNANT.

00:23.220 --> 00:25.313
THAT'S MY SON.

00:25.350 --> 00:27.011
OUR SON.

00:32.530 --> 00:33.849
YOUR BIRTHDAY'S COMING UP,

00:33.900 --> 00:35.527
AND WE STILL HAVEN'T DECIDED
WHAT WE'RE GONNA DO.

00:35.560 --> 00:36.891
WE CAN HAVE SOME OF YOUR FRIENDS
OVER HERE.

00:36.930 --> 00:38.568
PASTOR TIM AND HIS WIFE?

00:38.600 --> 00:41.660
I KIND OF WANTED TO TALK
TO YOU ALL ABOUT SOMETHING.

00:41.700 --> 00:45.158
WHAT I REALLY WANT THIS YEAR
IS TO GET BAPTIZED.

00:45.210 --> 00:48.407
SHE SET THIS WHOLE THING UP
SO WE COULDN'T SAY NO.

00:48.440 --> 00:52.046
IF YOU TELL HER NOW,
THIS WILL ALL BLOW UP.

00:52.080 --> 00:55.208
BUT AT LEAST SHE'LL KNOW
WHO SHE IS.

00:59.050 --> 01:02.520
Choir: * SHALL WE GATHER
AT THE RIVER *

01:02.560 --> 01:05.757
* WHERE BRIGHT ANGEL FEET
HAVE TROD? *

01:05.790 --> 01:08.918
* WITH ITS CRYSTAL TIDE
FOREVER *

01:08.960 --> 01:12.066
* FLOWING BY THE THRONE OF GOD

01:12.100 --> 01:15.365
* YES, WE'LL GATHER
AT THE RIVER *

01:15.400 --> 01:18.858
* THE BEAUTIFUL,
THE BEAUTIFUL RIVER *

01:18.910 --> 01:22.038
* GATHER WITH THE SAINTS
BY THE RIVER *

01:22.080 --> 01:25.743
* THAT FLOWS
BY THE THRONE OF GOD *

01:25.780 --> 01:29.580
[ APPLAUSE ]

01:31.420 --> 01:32.785
WELCOME TO

01:32.820 --> 01:36.221
THE REED STREET CHURCH
BAPTISM CELEBRATION!

01:36.260 --> 01:39.252
[ APPLAUSE ]

01:39.300 --> 01:42.463
UH, WE CALL THIS A CELEBRATION
AND NOT A CEREMONY

01:42.500 --> 01:45.924
BECAUSE THIS IS NO EMPTY RITUAL.

01:45.970 --> 01:49.235
WHEN WE IMMERSE OURSELVES
IN THESE BAPTISMAL WATERS,

01:49.270 --> 01:52.933
WE SYM BOLICALLY ALLOW
GOD'S GRACE AND FORGIVENESS

01:52.980 --> 01:54.607
TO WASH OVER US.

01:54.640 --> 01:58.076
IT'S THE BEGINNING OF A NEW LIFE
IN CHRIST.

01:58.110 --> 02:01.739
NOW WHEN I LOOK AT PAIGE,

02:01.780 --> 02:05.147
I AM REMINDED OF THAT VERSE
IN 1 JOHN --

02:05.190 --> 02:08.114
"LET US NOT LOVE
WITH WORDS AND SPEECH,

02:08.160 --> 02:11.129
BUT WITH ACTIONS AND TRUTH."

02:12.460 --> 02:14.428
PAIGE GIVES HER WHOLE HEART

02:14.460 --> 02:17.258
TO EVERY POLITICAL ACTION THAT
WE ENGAGE IN AT THIS CHURCH,

02:17.300 --> 02:20.497
WHETHER IT'S DRAFI'ING LETTERS
TO THE WHITE HOUSE

02:20.540 --> 02:23.304
TO DEMAND THAT PRESIDENT REAGAN
END HIS SUPPORT

02:23.340 --> 02:25.501
FOR THE DEHUMANIZING
RACIAL SEGREGATION

02:25.540 --> 02:26.973
IN SOUTH AFRICA,

02:27.010 --> 02:31.106
OR PICKETING THE INSANITY
AND WASTE

02:31.150 --> 02:32.777
OF THE NUCLEAR ARMS RACE,

02:32.820 --> 02:35.448
PAIGE IS ALWAYS
ON THE FRONT LINE,

02:35.480 --> 02:38.608
CHALLENGING,
QUESTIONING, YELLING.

02:38.650 --> 02:42.051
[ LAUGHTER ]

02:43.530 --> 02:45.157
BUT, PAIGE,

02:45.190 --> 02:49.798
THIS IS YOUR MOST DEFIANT
ACT OF PROTEST YET,

02:49.830 --> 02:51.821
BECAUSE TODAY,

02:51.870 --> 02:54.794
YOU MAKE A PUBLIC DECLARATION

02:54.840 --> 02:57.638
THAT YOU ARE A CHILD OF GOD.

02:57.670 --> 03:00.798
ARE YOU READY TO BE RENAMED
AND RECLAIMED

03:00.840 --> 03:02.171
IN THE NAME OF JESUS?

03:02.210 --> 03:04.678
ABSOLUTELY.
[ LAUGHS ]

03:09.520 --> 03:12.318
PAIGE JENNINGS,

03:12.360 --> 03:15.215
UPON PROFESSION OF YOUR FAITH,

03:15.260 --> 03:17.524
I BAPTIZE YOU NOW

03:17.560 --> 03:19.027
IN THE NAME OF THE FATHER,

03:19.060 --> 03:23.099
OF THE SON,
AND OF THE HOLY SPIRIT.

03:36.610 --> 03:38.009
[ EXHALES ]

03:38.050 --> 03:41.076
[ APPLAUSE ]

03:45.750 --> 03:47.786
Man: YEAH!

04:37.470 --> 04:39.779
Hans: WHITE HONDA.
NEW JERSEY PLATES.

04:39.810 --> 04:42.574
E-U-T-9-5-2-0.
[ SHIFTS GEARS ]

04:42.610 --> 04:43.804
Elizabeth:
WHAT ABOUT THE BLUE FORD

04:43.850 --> 04:45.101
ON WILLARD STREET?

04:45.150 --> 04:47.277
VIRGINIA PLATES.

04:47.320 --> 04:49.743
M-N-F...

04:49.790 --> 04:51.485
3-5...

04:53.360 --> 04:56.113
THAT'S CLOSE ENOUGH.
THAT'S GOOD.

04:56.160 --> 04:58.628
LISTEN...

04:58.660 --> 05:00.252
I WAS AT A STUDENT MEETING.

05:00.300 --> 05:02.962
AN ANTI-APARTHEID GROUP
THAT I GO TO.

05:03.000 --> 05:06.436
THERE WAS
THIS ONE UNDERGRADUATE -- TODD.

05:06.470 --> 05:10.304
HE REMINDED ME OF STUDENTS
I KNEW BACK IN JOHANNESBURG,

05:10.340 --> 05:13.832
HIRED BY THE GOVERNMENT
TO SPY ON THE REST OF US.

05:13.880 --> 05:16.178
I-I PROBABLY SHOULDN'T HAVE,
BUT I-I FOLLOWED HIM.

05:16.210 --> 05:18.770
AND?

05:18.810 --> 05:21.449
I THOUGHT I CAUGHT HIM
LOOKING FOR SURVEILLANCE.

05:21.480 --> 05:22.947
YOU THOUGHT?

05:22.990 --> 05:24.446
I-I BROKE OFF QUICKLY
IN CASE HE WAS,

05:24.490 --> 05:26.117
BUT I'M PRETTY SURE.

05:26.150 --> 05:29.119
MAYBE THE CIA THREATENING HIM
WITH THE SOUTH AFRICANS.

05:29.160 --> 05:31.458
REAGAN WOULD APPROVE THAT.

05:31.490 --> 05:33.492
HE -- HE CALLS
THE A.N.C. TERRORISTS

05:33.530 --> 05:36.966
WHILE SUPPORTING BOTHA
AND HIS MURDERERS.

05:37.000 --> 05:38.797
WE'LL LOOK INTO IT,

05:38.830 --> 05:41.697
BUT DO NOT FOLLOW HIM AGAIN
UNLESS I TELL YOU TO.

05:52.920 --> 05:55.411
YOU NEED SOME HELP?
SURE.

05:58.190 --> 06:00.317
SO... [ SIGHS]

06:00.360 --> 06:02.521
HOW DO YOU FEEL?
ANY DIFFERENT?

06:02.560 --> 06:05.654
UH...I GUESS. A LITTLE.

06:05.690 --> 06:08.727
MORE AT PEACE.

06:09.930 --> 06:11.488
UH, UP A LITTLE MORE.

06:11.530 --> 06:13.031
COMING UP.

06:15.070 --> 06:16.901
YEAH, RIGHT THERE.

06:19.580 --> 06:21.832
I'M REALLY PROUD OF YOU,
PAIGE.

06:21.880 --> 06:23.404
FOR WHAT?

06:23.450 --> 06:26.419
FOR BEING WHO YOU ARE --
STRONG --

06:26.450 --> 06:30.546
BECAUSE WE DIDN'T MAKE
THIS CHURCH THING EASY FOR YOU.

06:30.590 --> 06:32.512
NO, YOU DIDN'T.

06:32.560 --> 06:34.414
BUT YOU STUCK TO
YOUR BELIEFS.

06:37.460 --> 06:40.429
YOU CAN ALWAYS DO THAT,
YOU KNOW?

06:40.460 --> 06:42.018
STAND UP FOR WHAT YOU WANT.

06:42.060 --> 06:45.689
YOU SHOULD NEVER FEEL PRESSURE
TO...TO DO ANYTHING

06:45.730 --> 06:47.595
THAT YOU DON'T FEEL
IS RIGHT FOR YOU.

06:47.640 --> 06:49.062
I THINK IT'S CROOKED.

06:51.070 --> 06:53.538
IT'S STRAIGHT.
DID YOU HEAR WHAT I SAID?

06:53.580 --> 06:55.070
[ SIGHS ] YES, DAD,
I HEARD WHAT YOU SAID.

06:55.110 --> 06:58.045
I'M NOT GONNA DRINK
OR DO DRUGS.

06:58.080 --> 07:00.571
NO, I KNOW THAT.
SO THEN WHAT IS THIS ABOUT?

07:02.150 --> 07:05.711
IT'S ABOUT ALWAYS REMEMBERING
TO BE YOUR OWN PERSON,

07:05.750 --> 07:08.218
BECAUSE NO ONE KNOWS WHAT'S
BE'I'I'ER FOR YOU THAN YOU.

07:08.260 --> 07:11.627
EVEN IF...
THEY CARE FOR YOU

07:11.660 --> 07:14.549
OR HAVE YOUR BEST INTERESTS
AT HEART.

07:14.600 --> 07:17.728
YOU SHOULD ALWAYS BE TRUE
TO YOURSELF.

07:17.770 --> 07:21.228
GOING TO CHURCH IS BEING
TRUE TO MYSELF, DAD.

07:21.270 --> 07:23.807
I KNOW.
THAT'S NOT WHAT I MEANT.

07:23.840 --> 07:26.502
OKAY, DAD.

07:31.780 --> 07:34.078
I JUST WANT YOU
TO BE HAPPY.

07:34.120 --> 07:35.917
[ FLIPPING PAGES ]
THAT'S ALL.

07:35.950 --> 07:38.487
THAN KS.

07:45.130 --> 07:46.825
SO, TORI, WHAT DO YOU DO?

07:46.860 --> 07:49.249
I WAS
A HOSPITAL ADMINISTRATOR,

07:49.300 --> 07:51.120
BUT I'M IN BETWEEN JOBS
RIGHT NOW.

07:51.170 --> 07:52.933
A LOT OF PEOPLE ARE.

07:52.970 --> 07:55.097
YEAH. THINGS ARE
PICKING BACK UP.

07:55.140 --> 07:58.462
UH, VOLUNTEERING AT EST HAS
REALLY KEPT MY SPIRITS GOING.

07:58.510 --> 07:59.807
WHAT'S EST?

07:59.840 --> 08:01.808
ERHARD SEMINARS TRAINING.

08:01.840 --> 08:03.774
THAT'S WHERE WE ALL MET.

08:03.810 --> 08:06.108
WHAT KIND OF TRAINING
IS THAT?

08:06.150 --> 08:10.940
MM, PERSONAL. SPIRITUAL.
EMOTIONAL.

08:10.990 --> 08:12.685
SPIRITUAL? LIKE CHURCH?

08:12.720 --> 08:15.109
NO.

08:15.160 --> 08:17.788
WELL, DAD SAID IT WASN'T
A CHURCH.

08:17.830 --> 08:19.320
RIGHT, DAD?

08:19.360 --> 08:22.295
IT'S DEFINITELY NOT A CHURCH.
IT'S NOT EVEN RELIGIOUS.

08:22.330 --> 08:25.663
IT'S ABOUT BEING IN TOUCH
WITH WHERE YOU'RE AT.

08:25.700 --> 08:28.692
YOU KNOW, JUST BEING YOU,

08:28.740 --> 08:31.834
AND TAKING WHAT YOU GET
AND BEING COOL WITH IT.

08:31.870 --> 08:35.499
PEOPLE THINK CHURCH IS ALL ABOUT
FEELING SORRY FOR YOURSELF,

08:35.540 --> 08:37.303
BUT IT'S NOT.

08:37.350 --> 08:39.147
NOT AT MY CHURCH, ANYWAY.

08:39.180 --> 08:40.716
PAIGE JUST GOT BAPTIZED.

08:40.750 --> 08:42.980
OH. THAT'S COOL.

08:43.020 --> 08:44.817
LISTEN, WHATEVER WORKS.
RIGHT?

08:44.850 --> 08:48.149
I MEAN, EVERYBODY'S GOT
THEIR OWN THING. RIGHT?

08:48.190 --> 08:51.523
I JUST KNOW THAT EST
SAVED MY LIFE.

08:51.560 --> 08:53.653
HOW?
HENRY.

08:53.700 --> 08:56.191
NO. I DON'T MIND.

08:56.230 --> 08:59.859
I HAD A REALLY ROUGH
CHILDHOOD,

08:59.900 --> 09:01.993
AND EST HELPED ME FACE
WHAT HAPPENED

09:02.040 --> 09:04.338
AND. . . FORGIVE.

09:04.370 --> 09:06.736
HEY, MAYBE WE SHOULDN'T
TALK ABOUT THIS NOW.

09:06.780 --> 09:09.169
BUT WHAT IS IT?

09:09.210 --> 09:12.839
UH [SIGHS] IT'S A GROUP
OF PEOPLE WHO GET TOGETHER

09:12.880 --> 09:15.713
AND TRY AND HELP EACH OTHER OUT
WITH THEIR PROBLEMS.

09:15.750 --> 09:17.513
WHAT KIND OF PROBLEMS?

09:17.550 --> 09:20.553
[ UTENSIL CLINKS ]
GROWN-UP PROBLEMS, HENRY.

09:20.590 --> 09:23.024
SOUNDS WEIRD.

09:23.060 --> 09:26.188
YOU KNOW WHAT? IT KINDA IS.
[ LAUGHS ]

09:26.230 --> 09:28.721
[ CHUCKLES ]

09:36.970 --> 09:39.063
YOU HAVE TO EAT, NINA.

09:41.480 --> 09:43.277
PLEASE.

09:43.310 --> 09:44.709
MNH-MNH.

09:44.750 --> 09:46.775
JUST EAT SOMETHING.

09:48.950 --> 09:50.383
[ PLATE CLA'ITERS ]

09:50.420 --> 09:53.787
LOOK, YOU MADE A MISTAKE,
BUT...

09:53.820 --> 09:57.449
YOU HAVE TO STAY STRONG.

09:57.490 --> 09:58.923
FOR WHAT?

09:58.960 --> 10:02.760
I HAVE NOTHING.

10:02.800 --> 10:04.461
NO ONE.

10:06.600 --> 10:09.467
NO ONE?

10:09.500 --> 10:12.264
YOU SAID YOU HAD
A HUSBAND.

10:12.310 --> 10:14.073
I LEFI' HIM.

10:14.110 --> 10:17.978
HE WAS BEGGING ME
NOT TO.

10:19.350 --> 10:21.910
HOW CAN YOU LOVE SOMEONE
WHO LEAVES YOU?

10:21.950 --> 10:24.589
WELL,
IF YOU'RE IN LOVE...

10:24.620 --> 10:27.282
YOU STILL BELIEVE IN LOVE?

10:27.320 --> 10:28.753
AFI'ER ALL THIS?

10:28.790 --> 10:30.929
YES.

10:30.960 --> 10:32.325
OF COURSE.

10:32.360 --> 10:33.918
[ LAUGHS ]

10:33.960 --> 10:36.793
WHAT? WHAT ELSE IS THERE?

10:38.870 --> 10:41.088
MEN DON'T THINK LIKE THIS.

10:41.140 --> 10:42.664
ONLY US.

10:42.710 --> 10:44.769
WOMEN.

10:44.810 --> 10:48.678
IN AMERICA,
I HAD TWO LOVERS.

10:48.710 --> 10:52.441
ONE COMMUNIST,
ONE CAPITALIST.

10:52.480 --> 10:57.110
I WAS WHATEVER THEY WANTED ME
TO BE.

10:57.150 --> 11:01.189
I LOVED THEM BOTH
DIFFERENT WAYS.

11:01.220 --> 11:04.121
BUT AT THE END,

11:04.160 --> 11:07.152
THEY LOVED THEIR COUNTRIES
MORE THAN THEY LOVED ME.

11:17.870 --> 11:20.998
MMM. [ PANTS]

11:23.050 --> 11:25.006
MMM.

11:26.680 --> 11:28.341
[ MOANS ]

11:30.350 --> 11:31.988
WHERE ARE YOU?

11:32.020 --> 11:34.056
UH, MY HOUSE?

11:34.090 --> 11:36.854
NO. [ LAUGHS ]

11:36.890 --> 11:39.723
YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN.

11:39.760 --> 11:41.990
HMM?
WHERE'S YOUR HEAD AT?

11:42.030 --> 11:44.897
ARE YOU WITH ME IN THERE?

11:44.930 --> 11:46.363
Yeah.

11:46.400 --> 11:49.039
YEAH?
MM, YEAH.

11:57.610 --> 12:01.410
[ BOTH MOANING ]

12:09.760 --> 12:11.387
I DON'T THINK YOU ARE.

12:11.430 --> 12:14.888
AND IF WE'RE GONNA DO THIS,

12:14.930 --> 12:18.093
THEN I NEED YOU TO BE HERE.

12:18.130 --> 12:20.462
ALL OF YOU.

12:23.640 --> 12:25.369
I DON'T KNOW WHAT YOU WANT.

12:25.410 --> 12:27.708
I JUST WANT YOU TO
BE HONEST.

12:27.740 --> 12:29.947
ARE YOU THINKING ABOUT
YOUR EX-WIFE?

12:36.480 --> 12:38.380
SHE'S STILL MY WIFE.

12:38.420 --> 12:41.912
20 YEARS IS A LONG TIME
TO BE WITH SOMEONE.

12:41.960 --> 12:44.383
THIS IS OUR HOUSE.

12:44.430 --> 12:47.593
I'VE NEVER BEEN WITH ANYONE
BUT SANDRA IN THIS HOUSE.

12:47.630 --> 12:50.758
THAT MUST BE REALLY HARD.

12:50.800 --> 12:53.462
IT IS.

12:53.500 --> 12:56.936
BUT IT'S ALSO...
really good...

12:59.270 --> 13:01.773
...TO FEEL IT

13:01.810 --> 13:03.744
AND TO KNOW IT

13:03.780 --> 13:06.101
AND TO NOT PUSH IT AWAY.

13:06.150 --> 13:07.469
HMM?

13:07.520 --> 13:09.272
[ UNZIPS PANTS ]

13:11.350 --> 13:13.011
Yeah.

13:29.470 --> 13:31.335
DON'T PEEK.

13:31.370 --> 13:33.270
OKAY, I PROMISE I WON'T.

13:33.310 --> 13:35.278
GOOD. KIMMY.

13:35.310 --> 13:37.801
OKAY! OKAY. Okay.

13:42.550 --> 13:44.484
[ GIGGLES ]

13:52.690 --> 13:54.954
MM. NO.

13:55.000 --> 13:56.456
I'M BAKED.

13:56.500 --> 13:58.297
[ SIGHS ]
Lightweight.

13:58.330 --> 14:00.161
[ LAUGHS ]

14:04.240 --> 14:06.162
Ready?

14:06.210 --> 14:07.677
[ CLICK ]

14:11.380 --> 14:14.474
WHAT IS THIS?

14:14.520 --> 14:15.976
[ CLICK ]

14:16.020 --> 14:19.649
PINK FLOYD.

14:19.690 --> 14:22.659
JUST LAY BACK,
CLOSE YOUR EYES,

14:22.690 --> 14:23.987
AND TAKE IT IN.

14:24.030 --> 14:26.419
[ CLICK ]

14:29.700 --> 14:32.669
OH, MY GOD.

14:32.700 --> 14:34.839
[ LAUGHS ]

14:34.870 --> 14:36.497
THIS IS AMAZING.

14:36.540 --> 14:38.667
[ CLICK]
I know.

14:38.710 --> 14:40.371
[ CLICK ]

14:42.610 --> 14:44.749
[ CLICK ]

14:44.780 --> 14:47.271
I HAVE A BETTER IDEA.

14:48.880 --> 14:51.019
WHY DON'T WE TAKE A BATH
TOGETHER?

14:51.050 --> 14:55.054
COME ON. LIE BACK,
LISTEN TO THE MUSIC.

14:55.090 --> 14:58.218
NO, I REALLY WANNA
TAKE A BATH WITH YOU, JAMES.

14:59.760 --> 15:02.854
You take a bath.

15:02.900 --> 15:05.926
[ CHUCKLES ] NO.

15:05.970 --> 15:09.428
I'LL WAIT.

15:09.470 --> 15:12.564
YOU SHOULD BE RELAXED.

15:12.610 --> 15:15.078
OKAY.

15:32.760 --> 15:34.250
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

15:35.630 --> 15:39.418
[ WATER RUNNING ]

16:56.680 --> 16:58.045
MOM?

16:58.080 --> 17:01.379
PAIGE. I'M...

17:01.420 --> 17:03.980
YOU KNOW WHAT?
THIS IS RIDICULOUS.

17:04.020 --> 17:06.045
I...LOOK.

17:06.090 --> 17:08.388
SOMETIMES, I SMOKE,
AND...

17:08.420 --> 17:10.684
I KNOW YOU SMOKE.
HENRY KNOWS, TOO.

17:10.730 --> 17:13.858
WE'RE NOT CLUELESS, MOM.

17:13.900 --> 17:15.527
AND I'M NOT GONNA NAG YOU
ABOUT IT

17:15.560 --> 17:17.164
BECAUSE I KNOW YOU ALREADY KNOW
IT'S REALLY BAD FOR YOU.

17:17.200 --> 17:19.327
BUT I WILL SAY
THAT I WISH YOU DIDN'T

17:19.370 --> 17:21.031
AND I HOPE YOU QUIT.

17:22.740 --> 17:25.709
DON'T LOOK AT ME LIKE THAT,
MOM.

17:25.740 --> 17:27.731
LIKE WHAT?

17:27.780 --> 17:29.736
I DON'T KNOW. LIKE THAT.

17:29.780 --> 17:34.240
I'M... [SIGHS]
I'M JUST IMPRESSED WITH YOU.

17:34.280 --> 17:36.009
THAT'S ALL.

17:36.050 --> 17:38.689
YOU'RE JUST...ALL GROWN-UP
ALL OF A SUDDEN.

17:38.720 --> 17:40.711
CAN YOU EXTEND MY CURFEW
THEN?

17:40.760 --> 17:43.524
[ LAUGHS ]

17:43.560 --> 17:44.857
THAT'S A GOOD ONE.

17:44.890 --> 17:46.585
[ LAUGHS ] HAD TO TRY.

17:46.630 --> 17:47.927
[ CHUCKLES ]

17:47.960 --> 17:49.757
[ BREATH ES DEEPLY ]

17:49.800 --> 17:51.893
IT'S BEEN REALLY NICE
HANGING OUT WITH YOU, MOM.

17:53.740 --> 17:56.231
IT'S BEEN SO NICE
FOR ME, TOO.

17:56.270 --> 17:59.535
I KNOW THE CHURCH STUFF
ISN'T ALWAYS EASY FOR YOU,

17:59.570 --> 18:02.869
SO...THANKS
FOR SUPPORTING ME.

18:02.910 --> 18:07.119
PAIGE, I WILL SUPPORT YOU
NO MATTER WHAT.

18:07.150 --> 18:08.640
I HOPE YOU KNOW THAT.

18:11.620 --> 18:16.080
SO...WHAT DO YOU REALLY THINK
ABOUT CHURCH, MOM?

18:17.930 --> 18:19.727
WELL...

18:19.760 --> 18:22.627
THERE ARE PROBABLY
ONE TOO MANY POTLUCKS.

18:22.660 --> 18:24.560
[ LAUGHS ]

18:24.600 --> 18:27.933
WELL, WE CAN ALL AGREE ON THAT.
BUT, I MEAN...

18:27.970 --> 18:29.892
THE SPIRITUAL PART.

18:29.940 --> 18:32.329
YEAH.

18:34.810 --> 18:37.904
IT'S JUST NOT REALLY MY THING,
PAIGE.

18:37.950 --> 18:39.804
HOW DO YOU KNOW?

18:39.850 --> 18:42.569
I MEAN,
HAVE YOU EVER TRIED IT?

18:42.620 --> 18:45.509
WHAT?
PRAYING.

18:47.020 --> 18:48.419
NO.

18:48.460 --> 18:52.453
[ SIGHS ] IT'S --
IT'S SCARY AT FIRST.

18:52.490 --> 18:54.299
NOT SCARY. IT'S...

18:54.330 --> 18:57.094
KIND OF SILLY,
LIKE YOU'RE TALKING TO YOURSELF.

18:57.130 --> 19:01.999
BUT...AFTER A WHILE,
YOU -- YOU FEEL SOMETHING.

19:02.040 --> 19:04.600
WHAT?

19:04.640 --> 19:05.937
I DON'T KNOW.

19:05.970 --> 19:10.339
A...A PRESENCE.

19:11.980 --> 19:14.972
IT HELPS.

19:28.160 --> 19:29.718
[ THUD IN DISTANCE ]

19:31.830 --> 19:35.163
[ WATER DRAINING ]

19:51.050 --> 19:53.257
Kimberly: JAMES?

19:57.390 --> 19:59.654
HEY.
HI.

19:59.690 --> 20:01.829
WHERE WERE YOU?

20:01.860 --> 20:05.728
I WAS JUST GOING TO MY CAR
BECAUSE...

20:05.770 --> 20:07.499
I HAVE A SURPRISE FOR YOU.

20:07.540 --> 20:08.893
WHAT IS IT?

20:08.940 --> 20:12.262
WELL, GO AND WAIT IN YOUR ROOM.
I'LL GO GET IT.

20:20.210 --> 20:23.714
And no peeking.

20:25.250 --> 20:27.252
How much longer?
Five minutes.

20:27.290 --> 20:30.453
Give me your earrings.
Now.

20:42.570 --> 20:46.404
WHERE'S MY SURPRISE?
MM.

20:51.450 --> 20:53.441
I LOVE THEM.

20:53.480 --> 20:55.744
THANK YOU.

21:07.600 --> 21:09.420
[ GIGGLES ]

21:11.300 --> 21:13.268
How do they look?

21:13.300 --> 21:14.836
BEAUTIFUL.

21:33.490 --> 21:37.278
[ GIGGLES ]
YOU'RE A GOOD KISSER.

21:37.330 --> 21:38.786
[ TOWEL THUDS ]

21:41.960 --> 21:44.190
WHAT'S WRONG?

21:55.510 --> 21:57.307
I CAN'T.

21:57.350 --> 22:00.274
[ LAUGHS ] BUT MY PARENTS WON'T
BE HOME FOR HOURS, I SWEAR.

22:00.310 --> 22:02.278
IT'S NOT --
IT'S NOT YOUR PARENTS.

22:02.320 --> 22:03.719
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

22:05.490 --> 22:07.458
I WANT TO, BUT I...

22:07.490 --> 22:10.311
WHY? YOU DON'T WANT ME?

22:10.360 --> 22:13.329
N-NO.
I-I WANT YOU, KIMMY.

22:13.360 --> 22:16.454
BELIEVE ME, I WANT YOU.
BUT... [ INHALES DEEPLY ]

22:16.500 --> 22:18.161
JUST SAY IT.

22:22.670 --> 22:25.662
THINGS HAVE BEEN HARD LATELY.

22:25.710 --> 22:27.974
I'VE HAD A LOT OF PROBLEMS
AT WORK AND...

22:28.010 --> 22:30.649
SOME OTHER...STUFF.

22:30.680 --> 22:34.070
AND A GUY AT WORK TOLD ME ABOUT
A CHURCH HE GOES TO.

22:36.020 --> 22:37.840
I HADN'T BEEN TO CHURCH
SINCE I WAS A KID

22:37.890 --> 22:41.553
BECAUSE [SCOFFS]
I ALWAYS HATED IT.

22:41.590 --> 22:44.684
BUT I HAVE BEEN GOING
[INHALES DEEPLY]

22:48.030 --> 22:51.158
AND THE MINISTER TALKS ABOUT
STARTING OVER

22:51.200 --> 22:55.364
AND...HAVING A NEW LIFE
WITH GOD.

22:55.400 --> 22:57.231
AND [INHALES DEEPLY]

22:57.270 --> 22:59.568
I THINK I WANNA TRY THAT.

23:02.410 --> 23:04.878
WAIT. YOU'RE --
YOU'RE BREAKING UP WITH ME?

23:07.210 --> 23:09.349
NO. NO, I DON'T --
NO, I DON'T WANT TO.

23:09.380 --> 23:12.508
I-I-I HOPE
YOU DON'T WANT TO.

23:12.550 --> 23:17.351
I JUST NEED TO TAKE THINGS
SLOWLY. THAT'S ALL.

23:17.390 --> 23:18.789
IS THAT OKAY?

23:22.600 --> 23:25.524
SURE. BUT...

23:25.570 --> 23:29.768
ARE YOU SURE IT'S NOT ME?
I-IF I'M DOING SOMETHING WRONG?

23:29.800 --> 23:31.768
BECAUSE YOU CAN TELL ME.

23:31.810 --> 23:34.370
NO.
NO, IT'S NOT YOU AT ALL.

23:34.410 --> 23:37.208
YOU'RE...

23:37.240 --> 23:39.071
YOU'RE PERFECT.

23:44.490 --> 23:47.550
HE TOLD ME

23:47.590 --> 23:49.581
TO MEET HIM IN BRUSSELS.

23:49.620 --> 23:53.590
AFTER YOU LEFT THE PACKAGE
HE GAVE YOU?

23:53.630 --> 23:56.451
YES.

23:56.500 --> 23:59.799
I'VE NEVER BEEN TO BRUSSELS.

24:01.470 --> 24:03.609
THAT'S WHERE WE FIRST MET.

24:06.140 --> 24:09.303
WE BOTH MADE
THE SAME MISTAKE --

24:09.340 --> 24:11.979
TRUSTING THE MEN WE LOVED.

24:12.010 --> 24:16.947
NO, IT'S NOT LIKE THAT
WITH ME,

24:16.980 --> 24:18.743
NOT LIKE YOU.

24:18.790 --> 24:20.917
HE PUT YOU HERE.

24:20.960 --> 24:24.088
No.

24:24.130 --> 24:26.280
HE WOULD NEVER DO THAT.

24:28.030 --> 24:29.793
HE LOVES ME.

24:29.830 --> 24:33.129
He lied to you, Evi.

24:37.510 --> 24:39.637
He never lied to me.

24:44.810 --> 24:48.974
YOU DO THINGS FOR LOVE.

25:09.500 --> 25:11.730
HEY.
HEY.

25:19.050 --> 25:20.506
EVERYTHING OKAY HERE?

25:22.880 --> 25:25.986
THE CENTRE
WANTS US TO FOLLOW

25:26.020 --> 25:28.682
THAT 19-YEAR-OLD
SUPER SPY PROVOCATEUR

25:28.720 --> 25:30.517
HANS IS WORRIED ABOUT.

25:30.560 --> 25:32.255
[ SIGHS DEEPLY ]

25:34.860 --> 25:36.521
GREAT.

25:44.570 --> 25:48.006
[ LAUGHS ]

25:48.040 --> 25:49.507
REALLY?

25:49.540 --> 25:51.405
Yeah.

25:51.450 --> 25:54.544
[ LAUGHS ]

26:04.630 --> 26:08.396
[ DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE ]

26:10.060 --> 26:12.221
[ CHUCKLES ]

26:25.480 --> 26:26.970
[ CLOSES LIGHTER ]

26:30.580 --> 26:34.710
[ EXHALING DEEPLY ]

26:34.760 --> 26:37.627
[ SIGHS DEEPLY ]

26:37.660 --> 26:39.582
[ GRUNTS ]

26:39.630 --> 26:41.951
What?

26:42.000 --> 26:44.298
PAIGE.

26:44.330 --> 26:46.560
SHE THINKS I SHOULD
START PRAYING.

26:46.600 --> 26:50.730
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

26:50.770 --> 26:52.658
I would like
to see that.

27:07.520 --> 27:09.659
SHE'S LIVING IN
A FANTASY WORLD.

27:12.130 --> 27:13.449
I DON'T KNOW,

27:13.490 --> 27:16.823
BECAUSE JESUS REALLY
CAME THROUGH FOR ME TONIGHT.

27:20.700 --> 27:24.807
I TOLD KIMBERLY THE REASON
I COULDN'T SLEEP WITH HER WAS...

27:24.840 --> 27:27.331
[ EXHALES ]

27:27.370 --> 27:31.602
BECAUSE I HAD TO SERVE JESUS
INSTEAD.

27:31.650 --> 27:33.948
[ Laughing ] OH, MY.

27:33.980 --> 27:35.948
Yeah.

27:35.980 --> 27:40.349
[ BOTH LAUGHING ]

27:46.230 --> 27:47.788
[ CONTINUES LAUGHING ]

27:47.830 --> 27:50.651
Shh!
Shh, Shh, Shh, Shh!

27:52.000 --> 27:53.888
AHH.

27:56.870 --> 27:59.464
SO YOU DIDN'T...
sleep with her?

27:59.510 --> 28:01.671
No, I didn't.

28:03.850 --> 28:07.809
BUT IF THIS OPERATION
DRAGS ON AND...

28:07.850 --> 28:10.978
SHE GETS OLDER, THEN...

28:11.020 --> 28:13.818
MAYBE.

28:25.370 --> 28:29.192
[ WHIRRING AND BEEPING ]

28:30.040 --> 28:32.201
[ BEEPS ]

28:32.240 --> 28:34.379
NOTICE ANYTHING NEW?

28:34.410 --> 28:36.674
THERE'S NO CLASSIFIED FILES.

28:36.710 --> 28:38.371
AND THEY'RE NOT COMING BACK.

28:39.380 --> 28:41.018
MADE A COUPLE OF CALLS.

28:41.050 --> 28:43.371
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

28:43.420 --> 28:44.887
HEY, STAN.

28:44.920 --> 28:47.081
CAN I TALK TO YOU
FOR A SECOND?

28:47.120 --> 28:48.519
SURE.

28:48.560 --> 28:50.357
I WAS JUST TALKING TO
MY BUDDY DAN THOMPSON

28:50.390 --> 28:52.187
IN THE CINCINNATI
FIELD OFFICE.

28:52.230 --> 28:53.549
UH, WE WERE AT QUANTICO
TOGETHER.

28:53.590 --> 28:55.194
YEAH, HE SAID.

28:55.230 --> 28:58.063
SO I GOT SOME BAD NEWS.

28:58.100 --> 29:00.864
WE LOST FOUR GUYS
IN A SMALL PLANE CRASH IN OHIO.

29:00.900 --> 29:02.765
[ PAPER RUSTLES,
MAIL ROBOT BEEPS IN DISTANCE ]

29:02.800 --> 29:04.734
HE SAID YOU WERE FRIENDS
WITH ONE OF THEM.

29:06.970 --> 29:08.528
DAVE.

29:08.580 --> 29:11.208
WE WORKED OUT OF THE MIDWEST
BANK ROBBERY SQUAD TOGETHER.

29:11.250 --> 29:14.572
IT HASN'T BEEN ANNOUNCED YET.
JUST THOUGHT YOU'D LIKE TO KNOW.

29:14.620 --> 29:17.418
SORRY.
IF I CAN DO ANYTHING...

29:22.290 --> 29:25.453
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

29:25.490 --> 29:29.290
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

29:33.430 --> 29:36.092
[ DIALING ]

29:36.140 --> 29:39.439
[ Ringing ]

29:39.470 --> 29:41.233
Hi, this is Arthur.

29:41.280 --> 29:43.077
If you have a message
for me, Sandra, or Matthew,

29:43.110 --> 29:45.271
please leave your name, number,
and time of your call

29:45.310 --> 29:46.743
after the beep.

29:46.780 --> 29:48.771
[ BEEP ]

29:51.150 --> 29:52.811
[ RECEIVER CLICKS ]

29:56.290 --> 29:57.780
[ UTENSIL CLINKS ]

30:23.650 --> 30:26.346
NO LEFTOVERS?

30:26.390 --> 30:28.153
SORRY.

30:30.390 --> 30:32.278
[ TILES CLATTER ]

30:32.330 --> 30:34.491
[ SIGHS DEEPLY ]

30:34.530 --> 30:36.157
I GOT THE BUG IN.

30:36.200 --> 30:38.794
GOOD.

30:38.830 --> 30:40.468
HOW'S KIMBERLY?

30:40.500 --> 30:44.300
I THINK SHE'S NERVOUS ABOUT
A MATH TEST SHE HAS COMING UP.

30:44.340 --> 30:46.638
OH.

30:46.670 --> 30:48.877
DO YOU WANT SOME COFFEE?
SURE.

30:48.910 --> 30:50.229
[ TILES CLATTER ]

30:55.180 --> 30:57.671
HAVING WEEKLY UPDATES IS GOING
TO MAKE A BIG DIFFERENCE.

30:57.720 --> 30:59.039
THE MUJAHIDEEN
CAN BARELY FUNCTION

30:59.090 --> 31:00.512
WITHOUT AMERICAN ASSISTANCE.

31:00.550 --> 31:03.348
WEEKLY?

31:03.390 --> 31:06.223
CONDITIONS IN THE FIELD
WON'T SUPPORT THAT.

31:06.260 --> 31:08.694
HAS IT GOTTEN INTIMATE YET?

31:15.440 --> 31:17.362
YOU HAVE TO FORGE
A REAL BOND WITH HER

31:17.400 --> 31:19.402
IF YOU'RE GOING TO GET
TO THE RECORDING DEVICE

31:19.440 --> 31:20.839
WHEN YOU NEED TO.

31:20.870 --> 31:22.679
YOU KNOW THIS.

31:22.710 --> 31:24.075
YOU'VE KNOWN THIS
FROM THE BEGINNING.

31:24.110 --> 31:25.577
OUR SOLDIERASRIEV AFGHANISTAN

31:25.610 --> 31:28.044
I KNOW WHAT'S GOING ON
IN AFGHANISTAN.

31:37.090 --> 31:39.251
PHILIP, I WASN'T GOING TO
TELL YOU THIS

31:39.290 --> 31:41.053
UNTIL THINGS CALMED DOWN,

31:41.100 --> 31:44.092
BUT I THINK IT BEST
THAT YOU KNOW IT NOW.

31:44.130 --> 31:47.566
ABOUT A MONTH, WE CAPTURED IRINA
IN BRAZIL.

31:48.940 --> 31:51.568
SHE'S BEEN SENT HOME.
THERE WILL BE A TRIAL.

31:51.610 --> 31:55.728
I KNOW YOU SPOKE TO HER
ABOUT TWO YEARS AGO.

31:55.780 --> 31:57.372
SHE HAS A SON.

31:57.410 --> 32:00.243
HIS NAME IS MISHA.
HE'S 20 YEARS OLD.

32:00.280 --> 32:04.387
HE'S IN THE 345th
INDEPENDENT PARATROOP REGIMENT

32:04.420 --> 32:06.285
IN FAIZABAD.

32:06.320 --> 32:08.914
SHE SAYS HE'S YOURS.

32:14.330 --> 32:16.719
ONLY YOU KNOW IF IT'S TRUE,
PHILIP.

32:16.760 --> 32:19.399
BUT I'VE BEEN CHECKING ON HIM,
AND HE'S A GOOD SOLDIER.

32:19.430 --> 32:22.069
HIS COMMANDERS RESPECT HIM
A GREAT DEAL.

32:22.100 --> 32:26.605
HE'S LOYAL. HE'S TRUSTWORTHY.
HE'S LIKE YOU IN THAT RESPECT.

32:29.310 --> 32:32.347
I DIDN'T WANT TO HAVE
TO TELL YOU THIS WAY.

32:35.120 --> 32:37.111
HAVE YOU TOLD ELIZABETH?

32:37.150 --> 32:39.448
OF COURSE NOT.

32:59.040 --> 33:04.307
HANS' TEENAGE SPY LIKES REDHEADS
AND IS FAILING BIOLOGY.

33:09.320 --> 33:11.015
WHAT'S WRONG?

33:11.050 --> 33:12.540
NOTHING.

33:17.020 --> 33:20.126
NOTHING. I HAD A -- I HAD
A HARD MEETING WITH GABRIEL.

33:20.160 --> 33:22.355
WHAT HAPPENED?

33:25.200 --> 33:29.489
HE...TOLD ME...

33:29.540 --> 33:30.859
THAT I --

33:30.900 --> 33:33.869
HE'S TRYING TO HELP, PHILIP.

33:33.910 --> 33:35.707
WITH PAIGE.

33:35.740 --> 33:38.538
I KNOW IT'S A LOT
TO DEAL WITH,

33:38.580 --> 33:40.207
ESPECIALLY WITH
EVERYTHING ELSE GOING ON,

33:40.250 --> 33:41.808
BUT AFTER THE BAPTISM --

33:41.850 --> 33:44.887
I HAVE TO SWITCH THE TAPES
AT KIMBERLY'S WEEKLY,

33:44.920 --> 33:47.684
NOT MONTH LY.

34:02.370 --> 34:03.837
Orville Redenbacher: THEN POP
MY GOURMET POPPING CORN

34:03.870 --> 34:05.906
IN MY BUTTERY FLAVORED OIL.

34:05.940 --> 34:08.875
IT'LL TASTE BUTTERY
WITHOUT ANY BUTTER.
Sandra: HELLO?

34:08.910 --> 34:10.832
IN HERE.

34:10.880 --> 34:13.178
...AND FLUFFIER THAN OTHER
POPCORN, SO EACH TENDER MOR--

34:13.210 --> 34:14.575
[ TURNS OFF TV ]
WE SAW IT ON THE NEWS.

34:14.620 --> 34:17.077
[ REMOTE CLATTERS ]
I'M SORRY.

34:17.120 --> 34:18.917
THAN KS.

34:20.590 --> 34:22.114
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ] I'M SORRY.

34:26.560 --> 34:28.699
[ SNIFFLES ]

34:28.730 --> 34:30.220
HAVE YOU TALKED TO ELLEN?

34:30.260 --> 34:33.024
NOT YET.

34:33.070 --> 34:35.538
I TRIED TO CALL HER A COUPLE
TIMES. THE PHONE WAS BUSY.

34:35.570 --> 34:37.037
YEAH,
I'LL CALL HER TOMORROW.

34:37.070 --> 34:38.708
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]
OH, THOSE KIDS.

34:38.740 --> 34:40.139
Yeah.

34:42.410 --> 34:44.571
YOU MET HIM ONCE.
YOU REMEMBER?

34:44.610 --> 34:46.908
UH, YEAH. I THINK SO.

34:46.950 --> 34:50.078
DAVE WAS -- HE WAS...

34:50.120 --> 34:51.883
HE WAS JUST SO FUNNY.

34:51.920 --> 34:53.239
WASN'T HE?

34:53.290 --> 34:54.712
[ CHUCKLES ] HE WAS.

34:54.760 --> 34:56.387
[ CHUCKLES ]

34:56.420 --> 34:57.614
I MEANT TO CALL THEM, YOU KNOW?

34:57.660 --> 34:59.127
I MEANT TO CALL THEM
SO MANY TIMES.

34:59.160 --> 35:00.889
I JUST...

35:00.930 --> 35:02.727
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]

35:02.760 --> 35:04.899
CAN'T TAKE ONE MOMENT
FOR GRANTED.

35:04.930 --> 35:07.899
THERE'S GONNA BE A MEMORIAL
IN A COUPLE OF WEEKS.

35:07.930 --> 35:09.431
WILL YOU COME?

35:11.770 --> 35:14.477
I DON'T KNOW. UH...

35:14.510 --> 35:17.104
IT'S IN CHICAGO, ISN'T IT?

35:24.190 --> 35:25.680
I'LL THINK ABOUT IT.

35:27.950 --> 35:29.611
UM...

35:29.660 --> 35:32.925
I'LL SEE TOMORROW NIGHT.
MM-HMM.

35:32.960 --> 35:35.155
AND TAKE CARE OF YOURSELF.

35:35.200 --> 35:36.792
[ SIGHS DEEPLY ]

35:36.830 --> 35:38.468
DON'T KEEP IT ALL IN.

35:47.510 --> 35:50.934
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

35:50.980 --> 35:54.279
YOUR FRIEND HANS
IS ON TO SOMETHING.

35:54.320 --> 35:56.675
[ UTENSIL CLINKS ]

35:58.520 --> 36:00.181
THAT STUDENT YOU FOLLOWED

36:00.220 --> 36:03.189
MET WITH EUGENE VETER FROM
SOUTH AFRICAN INTELLIGENCE.

36:04.660 --> 36:06.628
ANY IDEA
WHAT HE'S DOING HERE?

36:06.660 --> 36:09.993
THE CENTRE HAS HAD INTERCEPTS
ABOUT THE N.I.S.

36:10.030 --> 36:11.463
PLANNING VIOLENT ATTACKS
IN THE US.

36:11.500 --> 36:14.469
TO DISCREDIT
THE ANTI-APARTHEID MOVEMENT.

36:14.500 --> 36:17.867
AND THEY THINK THAT YOU MAY HAVE
JUST FOUND THE MAN

36:17.900 --> 36:20.334
WHO'S GOING TO
CARRY THEM OUT.

36:22.010 --> 36:24.808
WHAT'S HE DOING MEETING WITH
AN UNDERGRADUATE?

36:24.850 --> 36:26.203
LOT OF
THE ANTI-APARTHEID MOVEMENT

36:26.250 --> 36:28.002
IS CENTERED
ON COLLEGE CAMPUSES.

36:28.050 --> 36:32.146
SO YOU THINK THEY'RE GONNA
BLOW UP A BUNCH OF KIDS?

36:32.190 --> 36:33.839
I THINK MR. REAGAN HAS MADE

36:33.890 --> 36:36.984
SOME VERY BAD FRIENDS
IN SOUTH AFRICA.

36:37.020 --> 36:39.523
THE WHOLE WORLD WATCHES
WHILE HE COZIES UP TO

36:39.560 --> 36:43.826
THE MOST RACIST GOVERNMENT
ON THE PLANET.

36:43.860 --> 36:48.695
AND WE ARE GOING TO BREAK HIM
WITH IT.

36:59.210 --> 37:01.872
PHILIP IS LOSING FAITH
IN ME.

37:08.890 --> 37:10.687
IT'S PAIGE.

37:10.720 --> 37:12.221
I KNOW.

37:16.230 --> 37:18.391
I NEVER WANT YOU TO
DECEIVE HIM,

37:18.430 --> 37:21.092
BUT IF HE'S HOLDING YOU BACK
ON THIS...

37:21.130 --> 37:24.531
HE KNOWS I'M GOING AHEAD
WITHOUT HIM.

37:24.570 --> 37:28.870
BUT YOU'RE NOT GOING AHEAD.

37:40.750 --> 37:42.115
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

37:42.160 --> 37:44.253
Girl: I KNOW! [ LAUGHS ]

37:44.290 --> 37:45.723
Boy: I LOST MY BACKPACK.

37:45.760 --> 37:49.628
WERE YOU SUPPOSED
TO PICK ME UP TODAY?

37:49.660 --> 37:51.924
A CLIENT RESCHEDULED
A TICKET PICKUP.

37:51.970 --> 37:53.460
YOU WANT A RIDE?

37:53.500 --> 37:55.092
SURE.

37:59.010 --> 38:01.308
NINA.

38:01.340 --> 38:03.774
I CAN'T SLEEP.

38:03.810 --> 38:07.906
JUST LAY DOWN,
CLOSE YOUR EYES.

38:07.950 --> 38:12.148
YOU HAVEN'T LOOKED AT ME
SINCE YOU CAME BACK.

38:18.660 --> 38:21.322
I'M LOOKING AT YOU NOW.

38:27.470 --> 38:30.598
EVERYTHING IS OKAY, YES?

38:30.640 --> 38:34.679
[ METAL DOOR ROLLS AND CLANKS
IN DISTANCE ]

38:34.710 --> 38:36.109
NINA?

38:36.140 --> 38:39.974
[ FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING ]

38:40.010 --> 38:41.841
NINA?
[ DOOR UNLOCKS ]

38:41.880 --> 38:43.973
NO.

38:44.020 --> 38:45.510
WHAT DID YOU DO?!

38:45.550 --> 38:49.111
NINA! NO! NO! NO!
[ SPEAKS RUSSIAN ]

38:49.160 --> 38:50.616
WHAT DID YOU DO?!

38:50.660 --> 38:52.628
NINA! NINA!
[ SPEAKS RUSSIAN ]

38:52.660 --> 38:54.525
NINA, WHAT DID YOU DO?!

38:54.560 --> 38:59.668
WHAT DID YOU DO?! [ SOBS ]
NINA, WHAT DID YOU DO?!

38:59.700 --> 39:01.793
NINA! NO!

39:01.840 --> 39:03.796
NO!
[ DOOR CLANKS ]

39:03.840 --> 39:06.536
[ EVI SCREAMING ]

39:06.570 --> 39:09.471
NO!

39:09.510 --> 39:13.241
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

39:18.850 --> 39:22.809
[ CHILDREN SHOUT PLAYFULLY ]

39:22.860 --> 39:25.328
HEY.
HEY.

39:25.360 --> 39:27.328
HOW WAS SCHOOL?

39:27.360 --> 39:29.828
IT WAS ALL RIGHT, I GUESS.

39:29.860 --> 39:31.157
I DON'T KNOW.

39:31.200 --> 39:33.828
STUPID. WHATEVER.

39:33.870 --> 39:36.668
CAN -- CAN WE GO SOMEPLACE
AND TALK?

39:36.700 --> 39:40.067
I'M KIND OF BUSY RIGHT NOW.

39:40.110 --> 39:42.374
I'M ONLY IN TOWN
FOR TODAY.

39:42.410 --> 39:46.369
I...I HAVE, LIKE, A BUNCH
OF STUFF I HAVE TO DO,

39:46.410 --> 39:49.277
AND --
I CAN'T STOP THINKING ABOUT YOU.

39:54.120 --> 39:56.884
[ CHUCKLES ]

40:00.090 --> 40:04.026
MY PARENTS WON'T BE HOME
UNTIL TONIGHT.

40:04.060 --> 40:07.689
YOU WANNA COME OVER?

40:07.730 --> 40:09.231
YEAH.

40:15.080 --> 40:19.744
[ SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE ]

40:25.120 --> 40:26.587
[ SHIFTS GEARS ]

40:28.120 --> 40:29.917
WHAT ARE WE DOING HERE?

40:29.960 --> 40:32.053
I WANNA SHOW YOU SOMETHING.
[ MAN SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY ]

40:32.090 --> 40:34.558
HERE?
[ DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE ]

40:34.600 --> 40:37.228
IT'LL BE OKAY.

40:37.260 --> 40:38.625
COME ON, LET'S GO.

40:38.670 --> 40:40.092
[ KEYS JANGLE ]

40:40.130 --> 40:43.497
[ MAN CONTINUES
SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY ]

40:51.310 --> 40:54.177
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

40:55.520 --> 40:56.942
COME ON.

41:00.820 --> 41:02.310
COME ON.

41:17.870 --> 41:20.134
CAN WE TALK FOR A SECOND?

41:22.480 --> 41:25.108
OKAY.

41:25.150 --> 41:27.971
I DIDN'T TELL YOU
THE WHOLE STORY BEFORE,

41:28.010 --> 41:30.808
ABOUT WHY I WENT BACK
TO CHURCH.

41:32.990 --> 41:35.618
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

41:35.660 --> 41:38.982
WHEN I WAS 17,
I GOT A GIRL PREGNANT.

41:39.030 --> 41:41.999
SHE RAISED HIM ON HER OWN.
SHE NEVER ASKED FOR ANYTHING.

41:42.030 --> 41:45.818
BUT HE'S GROWN NOW, AND I WANT
TO SEE HIM, BUT I CAN'T.

41:45.870 --> 41:48.293
BECAUSE WHAT COULD I SAY?
WHAT COULD I DO?

41:48.330 --> 41:49.695
I FAILED HIM.

41:49.740 --> 41:53.005
I NEVER TOOK ANY RESPONSIBILITY
FOR...ANYTHING,

41:53.040 --> 41:57.830
AND NOW I WANT TO.
I HAVE TO. I NEED TO...

41:57.880 --> 42:01.338
BECAUSE I WANT TO BE
A BETTER MAN,

42:01.380 --> 42:05.487
THE MAN THAT I COULDN'T BE
FOR MY SON.

42:05.520 --> 42:08.341
I WANT -- I WANT YOU
MORE THAN YOU KNOW.

42:08.390 --> 42:11.848
I WANT YOU, KIMMY,
BUT I AM...

42:11.890 --> 42:14.597
REALLY MESSED UP
RIGHT NOW.

42:16.060 --> 42:19.029
IT'S OKAY.
IT'S OKAY, JAMES.

42:20.900 --> 42:24.529
COULD YOU -- THIS IS
GONNA SOUND...CRAZY.

42:24.570 --> 42:26.037
WHAT?

42:28.070 --> 42:30.903
WOULD YOU PRAY WITH ME
RIGHT NOW?

42:36.380 --> 42:39.087
YES. I WILL.

42:49.730 --> 42:54.861
GOD, THANK YOU FOR BRINGING
KIMMY INTO MY LIFE.

42:54.900 --> 42:57.368
SHE IS SUCH A BLESSING.

42:57.400 --> 43:00.858
I AM SO CONFUSED
RIGHT NOW.

43:00.910 --> 43:04.277
PLEASE HELP ME
TO DO THE RIGHT THING

43:04.310 --> 43:07.746
AND...BE A BETTER PERSON.

43:07.780 --> 43:09.475
AMEN.

43:13.950 --> 43:16.054
AND PLEASE, PLEASE, GOD,

43:16.090 --> 43:19.582
PLEASE WATCH OVER JAMES' SON,
WHEREVER HE IS.

43:19.630 --> 43:22.428
AND PLEASE LET JAMES
SEE HIM AGAIN,

43:22.460 --> 43:25.293
BECAUSE I KNOW HE'LL BE
AN AMAZING FATHER.

43:25.330 --> 43:27.992
AMEN.

43:35.280 --> 43:38.943
THAT WAS AMAZING.

43:41.280 --> 43:43.942
IT WAS.

43:43.980 --> 43:45.413
[ MAN SHOUTS INDISTINCT LY ]

43:45.450 --> 43:48.419
WHAT ARE WE DOING HERE,
MOM?

43:48.450 --> 43:51.089
I HAD A GOOD FRIEND
WHO LIVED NEAR HERE.

43:51.120 --> 43:53.259
WHO?

43:53.290 --> 43:56.623
HIS NAME WAS GREGORY.

43:56.660 --> 43:59.299
DID DAD KNOW HIM?

43:59.330 --> 44:03.494
YEAH. WE ALL WORKED TOGETHER
IN THE CIVIL RIGHTS MOVEMENT.

44:03.540 --> 44:06.429
YOUR PARENTS WERE
REAL ACT IVISTS.

44:06.470 --> 44:09.473
AND GREGORY, HE WAS...

44:09.510 --> 44:11.944
HE WAS VERY IMPORTANT
TO ME.

44:11.980 --> 44:13.607
IMPORTANT HOW?

44:13.650 --> 44:16.972
[ MEN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY,
BASKETBALL BOUNCING ]

44:17.020 --> 44:20.148
HE HELPED ME SEE THE WORLD
IN A DIFFERENT WAY.

44:20.190 --> 44:21.953
HE...

44:21.990 --> 44:26.154
HE HELPED ME UNDERSTAND THINGS
I HAD ONLY READ ABOUT IN BOOKS.

44:27.990 --> 44:30.823
WERE YOU EVER ARRESTED?

44:30.860 --> 44:34.193
NO. WE WERE NEVER CAUGHT.

44:34.230 --> 44:36.892
LET'S SIT DOWN.

44:40.240 --> 44:43.334
WE DIDN'T JUST SING SONGS
AND MARCH, YOU KNOW.

44:43.380 --> 44:45.302
WE FOUGHT IN OTHER WAYS.
[ SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE ]

44:45.350 --> 44:47.375
WHAT OTHER WAYS?

44:49.180 --> 44:51.375
MOM.

44:54.020 --> 44:57.319
IT WASN'T ALWAYS LEGAL,
BUT IT WAS RIGHT.

44:57.360 --> 44:59.021
IT WAS RIGHT
FOR THE GREATER GOOD.

45:00.690 --> 45:03.659
WHEN DID YOU DO THIS?

45:03.700 --> 45:05.827
WHEN WE WERE FIRST MARRIED,

45:05.870 --> 45:08.168
BEFORE YOU WERE BORN.

45:08.200 --> 45:11.067
AND AFTER, TOO.

45:11.100 --> 45:13.660
YOUR FATHER AND I,
WE CARE ABOUT A LOT OF THINGS.

45:13.710 --> 45:17.430
IT'S NOT JUST ABOUT
THE TRAVEL AGENCY FOR US.

45:20.280 --> 45:22.919
I LOVE ALL THE GOOD YOU'RE DOING
WITH THE CHURCH,

45:22.950 --> 45:28.081
BUT SOMETIMES DOING GOOD
IS HARDER THAN...

45:28.120 --> 45:31.886
GOING TO RALLIES
AND SIGNING PETITIONS.

45:31.930 --> 45:33.886
YOU THINK
I DON'T DO ENOUGH?

45:33.930 --> 45:36.194
NO, THAT'S...

45:36.230 --> 45:38.357
I JUST...

45:38.400 --> 45:41.392
I THINK THERE'S SOMETHING
SPECIAL ABOUT YOU,

45:41.430 --> 45:43.534
AND I JUST THINK

45:43.570 --> 45:46.562
YOU COULD ACCOMPLISH
ANYTHING YOU WANTED TO.

45:48.910 --> 45:52.073
SO...WHAT, YOU BROUGHT ME
ALL THE WAY HERE

45:52.110 --> 45:54.908
TO TELL ME IT SHOULDN'T BE
IN THE CHURCH?

45:57.780 --> 46:00.544
NO, I BROUGHT YOU HERE

46:00.590 --> 46:02.558
BECAUSE I WANTED YOU TO KNOW

46:02.590 --> 46:05.753
THAT I'M MORE LIKE YOU
THAN YOU THINK.
